3. Results and discussion
The crystal structures of TiF3 and its analogs (WO3, ScF3, ReO3, NbF3, TaF3, and MoF3) have a cubic cell belonging to a space group of pm3m. Metal ions locate at the corners of the cube linked by anions. Each metal ion is coordinated by six anions, and each anion is bonded to two metal ions. The optimized lattice constants range from 3.795 Å

